// NIX-MIGRATION: placed RAW (home-manager out-of-store symlink) to keep niri
// hot-reload. Candidate to port to typed programs.niri.settings (niri-flake)
// later. Decision + rationale: ~/mecattaf/nix-decisions.md (D1).

// Machine-specific overrides. NB: under home-manager this file is deployed by
// the SAME whole-dir out-of-store symlink on every host (home.nix xdg.configFile
// "niri"), so anything uncommented here applies fleet-wide — keep per-host
// blocks commented out until a real per-host slot exists (post-first-boot niri
// nixification / programs.niri.settings is the candidate home for these).

// NIX-MIGRATION: drift-port of a deployed 2026-06-27 edit that lived directly in
// this machine's ~/.config/niri/config.kdl (in neither branch). HOST-SPECIFIC to
// the coordinator (this Framework desktop) ONLY — its DP-4 monitor is physically
// mounted inverted. Kept commented out because local.kdl is shared across all
// hosts (see note above); uncomment on the coordinator after flashing, or fold
// into its per-host nix config when niri gets nixified.
